     "label" -> "Quantum Mob/ Q3 Symbol", "language" -> "en", "paclet" -> 
    "QuantumMob/Q3", "status" -> "None", "summary" -> 
    "WickReset[ws, {k1, k2, ...} -> {s1, s2, ...} -> {t1, t2, ...}] applies \
on the input Wick state ws the projection operators corresponding to the \
occupation s1, s2, ... of the bare modes k1, k2, ... and then reset the bare \
modes to occupation t1, t2, .... WickReset[ws, {k1, k2, ...} -> {t1, t2, \
...}] takes measurement on the bare modes k1, k2, ... and then reset them to \
the occupation t1, t2, .... It returns the pair {val, out} of measurement \
outcome val and final state out. WickReset[{k1, k2, ...} -> ...] represents \
an operator form of WickReset to act on an input Wick state.", 
    "synonyms" -> {}, "tabletags" -> {}, "title" -> "WickReset", 
